re mistake, which throws away her advantage, due to e4. However, Bai Xue missed it. } 45... Qc7?! { Missing an important possibility: e4. This was also because of Bai Xue's fears of her opponent. } (45... e4! 46. Be2 (46. Nxe4?? Nxe4 47. Bxe4 Bxf5 48. Rh4 Qe5 49. Kf3 g5 50. hxg6 Bxg6 { With a passed pawn and massive pressure on the Be4. }) 46... Re5!? (46... Qf8!?)) 46. Ne4 { And from here on, she maintains full control of the position, and the finish should be near. } 46... Nxe4 47. Qxe4 Qd6 48. Kf2 Kc7 49. Rg1 Re7 50. h6 gxh6 51. Rg6 h5 52. Rh6 Rg7 53. Bxh5 Kb7 54. Bg6 { Mental and physical surrender. Qc7 put up much more resistance. } 54... Qf8?? (54... Qc7! { Puts up much more resistance, threatening the morsel on a5. } { [%csl Ra5][%cal Rc7a5] }) 55. Qe3 Kc7 56. Qh3 Kd6 57. Qh4 e4?? { The blunder that causes the collapse of her position. Now it's all over. } 58. Qh2+ 1-0


